	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ah, a poor young wood elf warrior named Ganweianie also helped to save this ancient artifact from evil Ogre. <br><br>Due to her relatively lower age (she was 30th when events started, and became 40th when events end) in legends world, she&nbsp;&nbsp;participated just only three times and had no chance to see that  artifact at all. She realized that one must have level 50+ at least to challenge those artifact.<br><br>Once she has been resed from Ebina at Qeynos dock after she failed battle with Durn Storncrash. Oh BTW, Ebina is very beautiful Erudite women cleric.<br><br>It was also wonderful news for her that Ebina got Mantle of Rallos Zek at last.<br><br>Congratulations on Ebina!<br><br>Homeless the beggar<br><br>P.S<br><br>Also Congratulations that the artifact is now called &quot;Ebina's Sundered Mantle of Zek&quot;. It is reasonable new name, because original Mantle of Zek was sundered when seals are broken and has first discoverer's name. Ebina told us in legends stormhammer bbs that its effect has been changed to Flowing Thought II from original Melee forcused Frenzy. It became now caster forcused item :p. I hope it will be available for all regular servers.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Jun 16 19:05:45 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
